I love this place for its cozy, boisterous atmosphere, and excellent selection of beers (especially the ones from Belgium). Its not particularly cheap, but its not expensive - the beers will vary in prices so there's something for everyone! The beer menu details out the various beers and their flavours so you can really pin down ones you'd be interested in. I love the fries, the mussels, and the schnitzel from here. 

Ideal for 2-6 people, unless you make reservations. It's often busy so you gotta watch out for game nights and that first couple of weeks of nice weather! 

Great spot, can't wait to come back here!